    <preface>
      <p>
        <docNumber>2025/10.</docNumber>
        <docTitle refersTo="#resolutionTitle">
          <span class="bold">	United Nations Interregional Crime and Justice Research Institute</span>
        </docTitle>
      </p>
    </preface>
    <preamble>
      <formula name="enactingFormula" eId="formula_1">
        <p xml:space="preserve">
          <span class="italic">The Economic and Social Council</span>,</p>
      </formula>
      <container name="Recognizing" eId="container_2">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recognizing</span> that nearly six decades have passed since the Economic and Social Council adopted resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/e/RES/1086(XXXIX)">1086 B (XXXIX)</a> on 30 July 1965, through which it called for an expansion of United Nations efforts in crime prevention and criminal justice,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Recognizing also" eId="container_3">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recognizing also</span> that this subsequently led to the establishment of the United Nations Interregional Crime and Justice Research Institute in 1968, which has since played a valued and integral role within the United Nations system, carrying out research and training in the domain of crime prevention, criminal justice and the rule of law,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Recalling" eId="container_4">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recalling</span> its resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/E/RES/2023/8">2023/8</a> of 7 June 2023 on the work on the Institute,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Acknowledging" eId="container_5">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Acknowledging</span> the increasingly transnational, organized and complex nature of crime, the continued scourge of terrorism and their combined far-reaching impact in terms of justice, the rule of law and sustainable development,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Mindful" eId="container_6">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Mindful</span> of the growing significance of the digital space in this regard, as well as the opportunities and risks presented by rapid technological advancements, including their potential for misuse,</p>
      </container>
    </preamble>
    <mainBody>
      <paragraph eId="para_7" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>1.</num>
        <content eId="para_7__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recognizes</span> the alignment of the United Nations Interregional Crime and Justice Research Institute with the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development<authorialNote marker="1" placement="bottom" eId="authorialNote_1"><p xml:space="preserve">	 	General Assembly resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/70/1">70/1</a>.</p></authorialNote> and the vision and approach of the Pact for the Future,<authorialNote marker="2" placement="bottom" eId="authorialNote_2"><p xml:space="preserve">	 	General Assembly resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/A/RES/79/1">79/1</a>.</p></authorialNote> particularly in promoting evidence-based policymaking, strengthening the rule of law and leveraging data-driven strategies to address transnational organized crime and terrorism;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_8" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>2.</num>
        <content eId="para_8__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Encourages</span> the Institute to continue to integrate its evidence-based and data-driven approach into its research, training and policy initiatives in support of Member States;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_10" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>3.</num>
        <content eId="para_10__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Notes</span> the efforts of the Institute to address the priorities set out in its Strategic Programme Framework for 2023–2026, and encourages the Institute to continue to implement its objectives while also initiating preparations for the development of its next Strategic Programme Framework for 2027–2030, ensuring its continued alignment with evolving global challenges, the priorities of the Pact for the Future and the needs of Member States;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_13" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>4.</num>
        <content eId="para_13__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Reiterates its deep appreciation</span> to Italy for hosting the Institute and facilitating its work in pursuit of its mandate and mission for nearly six decades;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_17" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>5.</num>
        <content eId="para_17__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Expresses further its appreciation</span> to those Member States and strategic partners that have supported or provided voluntary contributions to the Institute in furtherance of its mission;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_22" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>6.</num>
        <content eId="para_22__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Encourages</span> all organizations of the United Nations system to make full and effective use of the services provided by the Institute;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_28" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>7.</num>
        <content eId="para_28__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Appeals</span> to all Member States to consider providing voluntary support to enable the Institute to continue and expand its work, through research and training, to address the challenges identified in its Strategic Programme Framework for 2023–2026, noting the extrabudgetary nature of the funding of the Institute.</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
